    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-23",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-23",
      "title": "**A-23 Maximum Allowable Stress Values**",
      "content": "- (a) The maximum allowable stress values for materials used in the construction of pressure vessels shall be taken from Part M of this Standard. Specifically, allowable stress values for carbon and low-alloy steels shall be obtained from Table M-1 (see Part M). \n\n- (b) Allowable stress values are tabulated at discrete design temperatures. When a design temperature falls between two tabulated values, linear interpolation shall be used, in accordance with A-23(c). \n\n- (c) No extrapolation beyond the tabulated temperature range is permitted. If the design temperature exceeds the maximum tabulated temperature for a material, that material shall not be used. ",
      "page_number": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-23",
          "target_id": "tbl-m-1",
          "reference_text": "shall be obtained from Table M-1",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-25",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-25",
      "title": "**A-25 Corrosion**",
      "content": "- (a) A corrosion allowance (CA) shall be added to the minimum required thickness calculated by A-27 or A-32. \n\n- (b) The corrosion allowance shall be specified in the design datasheet and shall not be taken as less than zero. \n\n- (c) When back-calculating the Maximum Allowable Working Pressure (MAWP), the effective corroded thickness equals the nominal thickness minus the corrosion allowance. ",
      "page_number": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-25",
          "target_id": "fml-a-27-f0",
          "reference_text": "A-27",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-25",
          "target_id": "fml-a-32-f0",
          "reference_text": "A-32",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-27",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-27",
      "title": "**A-27 Thickness of Shells Under Internal Pressure**",
      "content": "- (a) The minimum required thickness of shells subjected to internal pressure shall not be less than that computed by the following formulas, per A-27(c) and A-27(d). \n\n- (b) The allowable stress S shall be obtained per A-23, and the joint efficiency E shall be obtained from Table B-12 (see B-12). \n\n- (c) Cylindrical Shells. ",
      "page_number": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "sec-a-23",
          "reference_text": "per A-23",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "tbl-b-12",
          "reference_text": "shall be obtained from Table B-12",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "fml-a-27-f0",
          "reference_text": "A-27",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-27",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-27",
      "title": "**A-27(c)(1) — Inside Radius Formula:**",
      "content": "```\nt=(P×R)/(S×E−0.6×P)\n```\n\nwhere: \n\n- t = minimum required thickness, mm \n\n- P = design pressure, MPa \n\n- R = inside radius of the shell course, mm \n\n- S = maximum allowable stress at design temperature, MPa (see Table M-1) \n\n1 \n\n- E = joint efficiency (see Table B-12) \n\nThis formula applies when: t ≤R/2 AND P ≤0.385 × S × E. When these conditions are not satisfied, the rules of A-27(c)(3) shall be applied (not covered here). ",
      "page_number": 1,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "tbl-m-1",
          "reference_text": "see Table M-1",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "tbl-b-12",
          "reference_text": "see Table B-12",
          "reference_type": "references"
        },
        {
          "source_id": "sec-a-27",
          "target_id": "fml-a-27-f0",
          "reference_text": "A-27",
          "reference_type": "references"
        }
      ],
      "table": null,
      "formula": null,
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
