    {
      "element_id": "sec-a-27",
      "element_type": "section",
      "paragraph_ref": "A-27",
      "title": "**A-27(c)(2) — Outside Radius Formula:**",
      "content": "```\nt=(P×Ro)/(S×E+0.4×P)\n```\n\nwhere Ro is the outside radius of the shell course. Applicable when P ≤0.385 × S × E. \n\n- (d) Spherical Shells. ",
      "page_number": 2,
      "parent_id": null,
      "cross_references": [],
